itemDescription: Welsh rugby union and rugby league footballer (1880-1971)

wikipedia_page.main: John "Jack" T. Jenkins (19 April 1880 – 1 December 1971) was a Welsh rugby union and professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1900s and 1910s. He played club level rugby union (RU) for Llwynypia RFC and representative level rugby league (RL) for Wales, and at club level for Warrington (Heritage № 139), as a stand-off or scrum-half, i.e. number 6, or 7.
